\fs20 HIGH LEVEL GROUP\par
\fs12 health, education, welfare.\par
\fs20\par
Dear Reader,\par
\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Thank you very much for buying this unique and special book. I wanted to take this opportunity to explain just how your support will help us to make a real difference to the lives of so many vulnerable chil\-dren.\par
\lang3081\par
\lang1033 More than 1 million children live in large residential institutions across Europe. Contrary to popular belief, most of them are \i not \i0 orphans, but are in care because their families are poor, disabled or from ethnic minori\-ties. Many of these children have disabilities and handicaps, but often remain without any health or educational interventions. In some cases they do not receive life\rquote s basics, such as adequate food. Almost always they are without human or emotional contact and stimulation.\par
\lang3081\par
\lang1033 To change the lives of institutionalised and margin\-alised children, and try to make sure that no future generation suffers in this way, J K Rowling and I set up the Children\rquote s High Level Group (CHLG) charity in 2005. We wanted to give these abandoned children a voice: to allow their stories to be heard.\par
\lang3081\par
\lang1033 CHLG aims to bring an end to the use of large institu\-tions and promote ways that allow children to live with families \endash  their own, foster or national adoptive parents \endash  or in small group homes.\par
\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The campaign helps around a quarter of a million chil\-dren each year. We fund a dedicated, independent child helpline that provides support and information to hun\-dreds of thousands of children annually. We also run education activities, including the \ldblquote Community Action\rdblquote  project, in which young people from mainstream edu\-cation work with special needs children in institutions; and \ldblquote Edelweiss\rdblquote , which allows young people who are marginalised and institutionalised to express them\-selves through their creativity and talents. And in Romania, CHLG has created a national children\rquote s council to represent the rights of children, and which allows them to speak out about their own experiences.\par
\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But our reach goes only so far. We need funds to scale up and replicate our work, to reach out into more countries and help even more children who are in such desperate need.\par
\lang3081\par
\lang1033 CHLG has a unique character amongst non\-governmental organisations in this field, namely working with governments and state institutions, civil society, professionals and voluntary organisations, as well as practical providers of services on the ground.\par
\par
CHLG aims to achieve full implementation of the United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child across Europe and, ultimately, around the world. In only two years, we have already assisted governments to develop strategies to prevent the abandonment of babies in hospitals and to improve the care of children with disabilities and handicaps, and have developed a manual of best practice in de-institutionalisation.\lang3081\par
